  given source→text ≡ "Cell is a self-bootstrapping metacircular language for LLMs. Programs are documents. Execution fills in values. The document IS the program IS the state. Cells start as natural language (soft) and progressively crystallize into deterministic code (hard) under oracle pressure. Cell is the Scheme of LLMs."
  yield spanish-text

  ∴ Translate «source→text» into Spanish. Preserve technical terms.

-- LLM evaluation:
-- Translating 6 sentences. Preserving "metacircular", "LLM/LLMs", "Cell"
-- as technical terms. Using standard Spanish computing vocabulary.

  yield spanish-text ≡ "Cell es un lenguaje metacircular auto-bootstrapping para LLMs. Los programas son documentos. La ejecución completa los valores. El documento ES el programa ES el estado. Las celdas comienzan como lenguaje natural (soft) y progresivamente se cristalizan en código determinista (hard) bajo presión de oráculo. Cell es el Scheme de los LLMs."

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ spanish-text is entirely in Spanish (except technical terms) → ✓
--     (Text is Spanish; "Cell", "metacircular", "LLMs", "Scheme", "soft",
--     "hard", "bootstrapping" retained as technical terms)
--   ⊨ spanish-text has same number of sentences as source→text → ✓
--     (6 sentences original, 6 sentences translated)
--   ⊨ "metacircular" appears in spanish-text → ✓
--     ("lenguaje metacircular" present)
