-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- frame 2: back-translate (soft cell, LLM translates Spanish → English)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

⊢ back-translate
  given translate→spanish-text ≡ "Cell es un lenguaje metacircular auto-bootstrapping para LLMs. Los programas son documentos. La ejecución completa los valores. El documento ES el programa ES el estado. Las celdas comienzan como lenguaje natural (soft) y progresivamente se cristalizan en código determinista (hard) bajo presión de oráculo. Cell es el Scheme de los LLMs."
  yield english-text

  ∴ Translate back into English. No access to original. Natural English.

-- LLM evaluation:
-- Translating from Spanish only. "Las celdas" → "The cells" (not "Cells" as
-- in the original, which uses "Cells" as a proper noun referring to program
-- units). "completa los valores" → "completes the values" rather than the
-- original's "fills in values". "presión de oráculo" → "oracle pressure" (exact).
-- "auto-bootstrapping" round-tripped intact.

  yield english-text ≡ "Cell is a metacircular auto-bootstrapping language for LLMs. Programs are documents. The execution completes the values. The document IS the program IS the state. The cells begin as natural language (soft) and progressively crystallize into deterministic code (hard) under oracle pressure. Cell is the Scheme of LLMs."

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ english-text is entirely in English → ✓
--   ⊨ english-text has same number of sentences as translate→spanish-text → ✓
--     (6 sentences)
--
-- All oracles pass. Freeze output.
