-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- frame 3: diff (soft cell, LLM compares original vs back-translation)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

⊢ diff
  given source→text ≡ "Cell is a self-bootstrapping metacircular language for LLMs. Programs are documents. Execution fills in values. The document IS the program IS the state. Cells start as natural language (soft) and progressively crystallize into deterministic code (hard) under oracle pressure. Cell is the Scheme of LLMs."
  given back-translate→english-text ≡ "Cell is a metacircular auto-bootstrapping language for LLMs. Programs are documents. The execution completes the values. The document IS the program IS the state. The cells begin as natural language (soft) and progressively crystallize into deterministic code (hard) under oracle pressure. Cell is the Scheme of LLMs."
  yield drifted-segments[], drift-score, acceptable

  ∴ Compare sentence by sentence. Identify semantic drift.

-- LLM evaluation:
-- Sentence-by-sentence comparison:
--   S1: "Cell is a self-bootstrapping metacircular language"
--    vs "Cell is a metacircular auto-bootstrapping language"
--    → Word order swapped, "self-" became "auto-". Minor lexical drift but
--      "self-bootstrapping" and "auto-bootstrapping" differ: the original
--      emphasizes self-reference (metacircular), the back-translation
--      suggests automated bootstrapping. An implementor could misread intent.
--      DRIFTED.
--
--   S2: "Programs are documents." vs "Programs are documents." → identical ✓
--
--   S3: "Execution fills in values." vs "The execution completes the values."
--    → "fills in" ≠ "completes". "Fills in" implies template-filling (blanks
--      get populated). "Completes" implies finishing/finalizing. An implementor
--      might build a "completion" system rather than a "fill-in" system.
--      DRIFTED.
--
--   S4: Identical ✓
--
--   S5: "Cells start as" vs "The cells begin as" → "start" ≈ "begin",
--      negligible. ✓
--
--   S6: Identical ✓

  yield drifted-segments ≡ [
    {
      original: "Cell is a self-bootstrapping metacircular language for LLMs.",
      back-translated: "Cell is a metacircular auto-bootstrapping language for LLMs.",
      drift: "Word order inverted; 'self-bootstrapping' became 'auto-bootstrapping', losing the self-referential connotation that connects to 'metacircular'."
    },
    {
      original: "Execution fills in values.",
      back-translated: "The execution completes the values.",
      drift: "'fills in' (template population) became 'completes' (finalization). Different mental model for an implementor."
    }
  ]
  yield drift-score ≡ 3
  yield acceptable ≡ false

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ drift-score ∈ {0..10} → ✓ (3)
--   ⊨ drift-score = 0 then drifted-segments empty → N/A (score ≠ 0)
--   ⊨ drift-score ≤ 1 then acceptable = true → N/A (score = 3)
--   ⊨ drift-score > 1 then acceptable = false → ✓ (3 > 1, acceptable = false)
--
-- All oracles pass. Freeze output.
-- Ready set after: { correct }

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- frame 4: correct (soft cell, retranslate drifted segments)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

⊢ correct
  given translate→spanish-text ≡ "Cell es un lenguaje metacircular auto-bootstrapping para LLMs. Los programas son documentos. La ejecución completa los valores. El documento ES el programa ES el estado. Las celdas comienzan como lenguaje natural (soft) y progresivamente se cristalizan en código determinista (hard) bajo presión de oráculo. Cell es el Scheme de los LLMs."
  given diff→drifted-segments ≡ [ {S1: word order + "auto-bootstrapping"}, {S3: "completa" → should be "fills in"} ]
  given diff→acceptable ≡ false
  given source→text ≡ "Cell is a self-bootstrapping metacircular language for LLMs. ..."
  yield corrected-spanish, changed-count

  ∴ Not acceptable. Retranslate drifted segments S1 and S3 from source→text.

-- LLM evaluation:
-- S1 fix: "Cell es un lenguaje metacircular auto-bootstrapping" →
--   "Cell es un lenguaje self-bootstrapping metacircular" — restored word
--   order matching original emphasis (self-bootstrapping first, metacircular
--   as modifier), kept "self-bootstrapping" as technical term.
-- S3 fix: "La ejecución completa los valores" →
--   "La ejecución rellena los valores" — "rellenar" = to fill in (as in
--   filling blanks in a form), which captures the template-filling semantics
--   better than "completar".
-- S2, S4, S5, S6: unchanged.

  yield corrected-spanish ≡ "Cell es un lenguaje self-bootstrapping metacircular para LLMs. Los programas son documentos. La ejecución rellena los valores. El documento ES el programa ES el estado. Las celdas comienzan como lenguaje natural (soft) y progresivamente se cristalizan en código determinista (hard) bajo presión de oráculo. Cell es el Scheme de los LLMs."
  yield changed-count ≡ 2

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ if acceptable then corrected = translate→spanish-text → N/A (not acceptable)
--   ⊨ if acceptable then changed-count = 0 → N/A
--   ⊨ if not acceptable then changed-count > 0 → ✓ (2 > 0)
--   ⊨ corrected-spanish is in Spanish (except technical terms) → ✓
--
-- All oracles pass. Freeze output.
--
-- ⊢∘ refine: iteration 1 complete.
--   diff→acceptable = false → continue loop.
